UBUNTU LINUX

1. Decide location and URL by setting environment variables used below...
For a developer...
  export WB_ROOT=~/projects/whooshingby
  export HOST=whooshingby [also edit /etc/hosts to alias "whooshingby" to 127.0.0.1]
For production...
  export WB_ROOT=/opt/whooshingby
  export HOST=whooshingby.com

2. Run these commands to set up apache, php, phpunit, and whooshingby:
Apache:  
  sudo apt-get install apache2
PHP:
  sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-php5
PHPUnit: 
  sudo apt-get install pear
  sudo apt-get upgrade pear
  sudo pear channel-discover pear.phpunit.de
  sudo pear channel-discover pear.symfony-project.com
  sudo pear channel-discover components.ez.no
  sudo pear update-channels
  sudo pear upgrade-all
  sudo pear install --alldeps phpunit/PHPUnit
Whooshingby: 
  sudo mkdir $WB_ROOT
  sudo chown $USER $WB_ROOT
  cd $WB_ROOT/..
  git clone git@github.com:douglassquirrel/whooshingby.git
  sed -e "s:@WB_ROOT:$WB_ROOT:g" -e "s:@HOST:$HOST:g" $WB_ROOT/install/whooshingby.conf | sudo tee /etc/apache2/sites-available/whooshingby.conf
  sudo a2ensite whooshingby.conf
  sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 reload

3. Run tests:
  cd $WB_ROOT
  phpunit test

4. Visit http://$HOST and verify whooshingby is running


